Pushed successfully to main (`67000a0..fb680d8`).

I added the **Blue Hole (Dahab)** — one of the most famous and heavily-searched dive sites on Earth, and a genuine gap (the existing "Blue Hole" entries were Palau, Gozo, and Belize; the Red Sea Sinai one was missing).

What I verified and chose:
- **Pick rationale:** `coverage-gaps.json` was partly stale (its top regional picks — Zenobia, Elphinstone, Dunraven, Carnatic, Giannis D — are already in `sites.json`). The Dahab Blue Hole was a true missing world-class site. Mapped to `ras-mohammed-egypt`, the same loose South Sinai hub the dataset already uses for far-flung Sinai/Gubal sites like Thistlegorm.
- **Facts** cross-checked against Wikipedia + dive sources: coords 28.5722, 34.5374; the Saddle (~6 m), the Arch (26 m tunnel, ceiling 55 m, floor 120 m), hole >100 m; seasonal temps/viz; reef species; "deadliest dive site" reputation.
- **Hero image:** rejected the iconic Arch shot (only 800×600) and a topside parking-lot photo (5277px but not underwater), choosing `Free_divers_at_the_Blue_Hole_2.jpg` (2651×2675, CC BY 2.0, verified HTTP 200) — an underwater shot of freedivers descending the reef wall into the deep blue, matching the description's lead on the site's fame as a shore freediving site.
- **Integrity:** JSON parses, no duplicate IDs, 12 monthly conditions entries, description 750 chars, diff purely additive (+242 lines).

